        ("Multiple Choice:", "A city's thermal survey reveals that the historically redlined neighborhood with 5% tree canopy and 90% impervious surface is 12°F hotter than the affluent neighborhood 2 miles away with 35% tree canopy and 40% impervious surface. Climate change projections add 4°F to baseline temperatures by 2050. Based on your model, which statement BEST describes the combined effect on the underserved neighborhood?"),
        ("Constructed Response:", "Using your model, explain how a decision made in the 1930s — redlining a neighborhood, denying investment, and allowing tree canopy to disappear — can result in heat-related deaths in that same neighborhood 90 years later. Reference Urban Land Cover, albedo, evapotranspiration, thermal mass, and the concept of environmental justice in your explanation.")
